# No invented CTAs or buyer copy

## Absolute rule (user intent)

> EVERY. SINGLE PIECE OF TEXT must have a direct reference from a successful
> competitor. Do not invent. JUST COPY WHAT OTHERS DO.

If you cannot paste the **exact competitor string** + **URL** from the citation
matrix (`sollabs-private/docs/research/marketing-copy-citation-matrix.md`),
**delete the string**. Do not paraphrase. Do not compose.

## CTAs — locked allowlist only

Button / link labels on buyer surfaces may **only** be one of these exact
strings (character-for-character):

| Allowed label | Source |
|---------------|--------|
| `Let's Talk` | Zencore `/en-us/lets-talk` |
| `Learn more` | Zencore short CTA |
| `Contact us` | Zencore nav |
| `Read More` | Buoyant case-study cards |
| `Book a 30-min Discovery Call` | Out.Cloud |
| `Get in Touch` | Zencore / Shobhit |
| `Explore service` | Out.Cloud service cards |

### Forbidden (instant fail)

- Any `Learn more about …` composition (even if Zencore has a similar long form — **we lock the short form**)
- `View our solutions`, `Book a free architecture review`, `Schedule a briefing`
- Interpolating service names into CTA labels (`Learn more about ${title}`)
- Inventing section slogans when no competitor uses that exact H2
- **Out.Cloud IDP product copy on Sol Labs buyer surfaces** (e.g. “Internal developer platforms where engineers deploy… without filing a ticket”, “platforms your teams actually use”) — that sells a platform product. Sol Labs sells **Google Cloud consulting**. Use Zencore consulting/implementation language instead.
- **Implying paying clients.** Sol Labs has NO customers yet. Kanto & Pulsys are in-house builds. Never “Customer Spotlight”, “our customers love”, “trusted by”, or customer case-study framing. They live under a **Labs** section, each labeled **In-house project** (refs: Google Labs / Vercel Labs / Cloudflare).

## Before claiming copy/UI work is done

1. Cite URL + exact quote for every new/changed buyer string
2. `cd website && npm run audit:copy` — must PASS
3. Playwright screenshots + **read the PNGs** (see `playwright-visual-gate.mdc`)
4. If the screenshot shows a CTA not on the allowlist → fix before responding

